# Dashboard UI

## Stack

- Next.js 16 App Router — read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before assuming APIs from training data.
- Tailwind v4 + Shadcn primitives in `components/ui/`.
- Server pages fetch data; interactive pieces are `"use client"` components.

## Conventions

- Page headings: `page-heading`, `page-subheading`, `section-heading` (see `globals.css`).
- Forms: call API routes via `fetch`, show errors inline, `router.refresh()` after mutations.
- Prefer Shadcn `Card`, `Table`, `Badge`, `Button` over bespoke markup.
- New Shadcn component: `cd apps/web && npx shadcn@latest add <name>`

## Data flow

- Dashboard metrics: server component loads `getProjectMetrics()` → passes props to client panels.
- LLM panel polls `GET /api/projects/[id]/analyze` while status is `PENDING`/`RUNNING`.
- Hide stale suggestions during an active run; show progress bar with `completedSteps / totalSteps`.

## Don't

- Import `lib/api.ts` or `@triage-ops/db` from client components (use API routes).
- Parse markdown to HTML for issue descriptions — show raw markdown in `<pre>` for previews.
